<!-- Node: "In Soviet Russia Videos Play Half-Life." -->
<div class="body_box_header">In Soviet Russia Videos Play Half-Life.</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/31" title="View user profile.">mazemaster</a> on Wednesday, June 9, 2004 - 21:01</small><br /><br />
Ever wanted to add a working TV set to your map? Now you can.<br />
<br />
 <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/">AviKit</a> has released a mod <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/avikit.zip">code kit</a> to allow .avi playback in your Half-Life mod. This is not some kludgy hack, this is real-time video playback on map objects in Half-Life. <a href="http://collective.valve-erc.com/index.php?news=1086730872-55251400">More info</a> is available at the <a href="http://collective.valve-erc.com">VERC</a>. <a href="http://www.bits.bris.ac.uk/randomnine/projects/avikit/akhl1.jpg">Screenshot</a>.
