</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Code Locks in Half-Life" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Code Locks in Half-Life</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Monday, June 7, 2004 - 20:05</small><br /><br />
Sebastiannielsen has just posted a tutorial on the RUST website called <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Locks</a>. Several techniques exist to make doors with code locks, but I think this is by far the easiest and most exciting method todate. Sebastiannielsen points out that the code locks will be cool in multiplayer maps, where the developer can have a "code" to enter a protect-room (full with weapons). Imagine a button to open a door with lava under all the other players. Why not a turret or use your imagination! Check out Sebastiannielsen's <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/290">Code Lock Tutorial</a>
<br /><br />
